<title>American BBQ SpareRibs</title>
<filename>american_bbq_spareribs.xml</filename>
<thumbnail>spare_ribs.jpeg</thumbnail>
<category>Pork</category>
<category>Dinner</category>
<category>Lunch</category>
<diet>GlutenFree</diet>
<diet>Paleo</diet>
<diet>DiaryFree</diet>
<diet>EggFree</diet>
<yield>6</yield>
<prepTime>P1D20M</prepTime>
<cookTime>PT15M</cookTime>
<ingredient>1.8 kg Pork Spare Ribs</ingredient>
<ingredient>6 tbsp tomatoe sauce</ingredient>
<ingredient>3 tbsp honey</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 tbsp red wine vinegar</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 tbsp mustard</ingredient>
<ingredient>S and P to taste</ingredient>
<step>Cut ribs then boil in large pot for 20 minutes and drain well.</step>
<step>Mix all other ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.</step>
<step>Place meat and marinate in large marinating container.</step>
<step>Ensure all meat is covered.</step>
<step>Leave overnight, but turn occasionally.</step>
<step>Cook on BBQ and serve with corn on the cob and Spanish rice.</step>
</recipe>

